        "KSL": "Kagyu Samye Ling Monastery",
        "about-text": "The Tsurlug Astrological Tradition began with The Compendium of Astrology formulated by the Third Karmapa Rangjung Dorje in 1318. Following in his footsteps, Tsurpu Jamyang Chenpo composed a major astrological treatise in 1497. Trinleypa Chokle Namgyal and Pawo Tsuklak Trengwa both commented on Rangjung Dorje\"s text. This subsequently came to be known as Tsurlug (Tsurpu Tradition) and gained adherents in the whole of Tibet following its major propagation by Situ Penchen in Eastern Tibet. In 1732, his nephew Karma Ngelek Tenzin wrote The Excellent Vase of Practical Usage and since then we have what is now known as Tsurlug Drubtsi (Siddhanta Astrological System of Tsurpu).",
